Q. Can you create a program to check whether a number is positive or negative or 0?

If number is positive, print "The number is positive"
If number is negative, print "The number is negative"
(and) If number is 0, print "The number is 0"Q. Can you create a program to check whether a number is positive or negative or 0?

#include <stdio.h>
/**
 * creating a program that checks whether a number is positive,negative or 0
 * %lf is the format specifier of an double(data type);
 * this code use if else condition.
 */
 int main ()
 {
     double number;
     printf("Ã‰nter a number: ");
     scanf("%lf", &number);
     
      if (number > 0) 
     {
     printf("Its a positive number.");
     }
     else if(number < 0)
     {
        printf("its a Negative number.");
     }
     else 
     {
         printf("Number is 0");
     }
       return (0);
}
